What's New with Woo
"Human beings are not standardized."
Accessibility is a priority for WooCommerce, both in our work this year and on our roadmap going forward. With new EU regulations on the way, we sat down with Amber and Chris Hinds of Equalize Digital to discuss recent improvements and developer best practices.
Get insights on accessibility

New in our Marketplace

Seamless omnichannel power
Help clients sell across channels when they power their operations with Linnworks Advanced.
Clients can keep a real-time eye on inventory, automate essential tasks, and rest assured that orders and stock levels are accurate and efficiently managed across the board.
Simplify their operation
Simplify their operation

Leave competitors in the dust
When customers wait for a page to load, every second counts. Literally.
Supercharge your clients' site speed with WP Rocket to decrease bounce rates, create solid first impressions, and boost their search rankings and Core Web Vitals scores.
Prepare for liftoff
Prepare for liftoff

New in WooCommerce 9.2
  • Say hi to a more personalized homepage! You can now add, remove, shuffle, and rearrange multiple ecommerce-oriented patterns to create the exact experiences brands and customers want.
  • To increase conversions, stock will now only be held once a customer attempts to make a payment, rather than when an item is added to cart. If payment fails, stock is freed up instantly.

Bite-sized updates
  • WooCommerce is built for scaling. Read our new guide to walk through every step of scaling a business - from first sale to enterprise-level order volume.
  • Looking to be a featured agency in our brand new partner directory? Reach out to Automattic for Agencies to learn more.
  • WordCamp US is around the corner - will we see you in Portland next month? Make sure you swing by our booth to say hi (and get some rad Woo swag, of course).

Run your store from anywhere
